data.title: Is Curiosity All You Need? On the Utility of Emergent Behaviours from Curious Exploration
data.description: We argue that merely using curiosity for fast environment exploration or as a bonus reward for a specific task does not harness the full potential of this technique and misses useful skills. Instead, we propose to shift the focus towards retaining the behaviours which emerge during curiosity-based learning. We posit that these self-discovered behaviours serve as valuable skills in an agent’s repertoire to solve related tasks.
